## Step 1: Recall the formula for combinations
$\dbinom{n}{r} = \dfrac{n!}{r!(n-r)!}$
## Step 2: Substitute n = 11 and r = 8 into the combination formula
$\dbinom{11}{8} = \dfrac{11!}{8!(11-8)!}$
## Step 3: Simplify the factorial terms in the combination formula
$\dbinom{11}{8} = \dfrac{11!}{8!3!}$
## Step 4: Calculate the factorials and simplify the expression
$\dbinom{11}{8} = \dfrac{11 \times 10 \times 9}{3 \times 2 \times 1}$
## Step 5: Perform the multiplication in the numerator and denominator
$\dbinom{11}{8} = \dfrac{990}{6}$
## Step 6: Divide the numerator by the denominator to get the result
$\dbinom{11}{8} = 165$
## Step 7: Final Answer: $\boxed{165}$
